DuplicateRecordSet.name: DuplicateRecordSet
DuplicateRecordSet.description: Represents a group of records that have been identified as duplicates. Each duplicate record set contains one or more duplicate record items. Use this object to create custom report types and view the results of duplicate jobs.

DuplicateRuleId.description: The duplicate rule used to identify this list of duplicate records.

LastReferencedDate.description: The timestamp when the current user last accessed this record, a record related to this record, or a list view.

LastViewedDate.description: The timestamp when the current user last viewed this record or list view. If this value is null, the user might have only accessed this record or list view (LastReferencedDate) but not viewed it.

Name.description: The autogenerated name thatâ€™s given to the duplicate record set. Label is Duplicate Record Set Name.

RecordCount.description: The number of record items in the set.

ParentId.description: The ParentId represents the parent of a duplicate rule or duplicate job. A ParentId is polymorphic. The label is Parent. This field is available in API versions 42.0 and later.
